h4. Additional Background

I've attached a .zip file with the reproducible project.

The following query:

 
{code:java}
collection.AsQueryable().Where(x => x.BooleanPropertyRepresentedAsInt32)
{code}
should be translated as:

 

 
{code:java}
{ $match : { BooleanPropertyRepresentedAsInt32 : 1 } }
{code}
not as:

 
{code:java}
{ $match : { BooleanPropertyRepresentedAsInt32 : true } } {code}
The `true`  constant must be serialized with the serializer configured for the property.

CSHARP-4669 noted high memory usage when using FLE with GridFS. A forums user [noticed the following|https://www.mongodb.com/community/forums/t/clientencryption-encrypt-in-c-uses-a-lot-of-memory-relative-to-a-somewhat-large-file/229871/7]:

{quote}
The {{EncryptField}} and {{EncryptFieldAsync}} methods both call {{UnwrapValue}}, which is:

{code}
private BsonValue UnwrapValue(byte[] encryptedWrappedBytes)
{
    var rawDocument = new RawBsonDocument(encryptedWrappedBytes);
    return rawDocument["v"];
}
{code}

As {{RawBsonDocument}} is {{IDisposable}}, it should be surrounded by a using clause:

{code}
private BsonValue UnwrapValue(byte[] encryptedWrappedBytes)
{
    using var rawDocument = new RawBsonDocument(encryptedWrappedBytes);
    return rawDocument["v"];
}
{code}
{quote}

We should implement this improvement and verify that it reduces memory usage when using FLE with large documents such as GridFS.

CombinedProjectionDefinition.Render() method throws StackOverflowException when including a huge number of fields.

Here is a unit test reproducing the error:

{code:csharp}
[Fact]
public void Include_Many_Fields()
{
    var subject = CreateSubject<Person>();
 
    var projection = subject.Include(x => x.FirstName);
    var expectedProjection = new StringBuilder("{fn: 1");
    for (int i = 0; i < 10000; i++)
    {
        var field = $"Field{i}";
        projection = projection.Include(field);
        expectedProjection.Append($", {field}: 1");
    }
    expectedProjection.Append("}");
 
    Assert(projection, expectedProjection.ToString());
}
{code}

To fix the isuue I changed the constructor of the CombinedProjectionDefinition class to "unwind" the _projections collection to avoid recursively calling the Render() method:

{code:csharp}
public CombinedProjectionDefinition(IEnumerable<ProjectionDefinition<TSource>> projections)
{
    _projections = Ensure.IsNotNull(projections, nameof(projections))
        .SelectMany(projection => (projection as CombinedProjectionDefinition<TSource>)?._projections ?? new List<ProjectionDefinition<TSource>> { projection })
        .ToList();
}
{code}

Let me know if you need more information to fix the issue or if you want me to also create a pull request.

